name: Λｒｇｏ░Ｎａｖｉｓ
description: The Argonauts (/ˈɑːrɡənɔːt/; Ancient Greek: Ἀργοναῦται, Argonautai, 'Argo sailors') were a band of heroes in Greek mythology, who in the years before the Trojan War (around 1300 BC)[1] accompanied Jason to Colchis in his quest to find the Golden Fleece. This is a remix of Bertel Thorvaldsen (1770-1844) sculpture. 1900 x 1900px, Mp4, 2018
